SIMPLE: sufferer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sufferer
<hw>Suf"fer*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
suffers; one who endures or undergoes suffering; one who sustains
inconvenience or loss; <as>as, <ex>sufferers</ex> by poverty or
sickness; men are <ex>sufferers</ex> by fire or by losses at
sea.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who permits or allows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suffering</ent>⟦br⟧
